   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/acadian/Racca_Lorita_T731.abs.pdf">Racca discusses her family; her weaving, including learning to weave, the people
            she worked with, the materials and equipment she used, the weaving process, and prices
            fetched for rugs and blankets; doing weaving demonstrations in Alexandria and
            Shreveport; and attending the opening of an exhibit at the New Orleans Museum of
            Art.</abstract>
